Deprecated API

Contents

  • Deprecated Classes
  • Deprecated Methods
  • Deprecated Classes 
    Class and Description
    com.github.xemiru.sponge.boxboy.button.ToggleButton
    This version of a ToggleButton was designed in a very confusing way when put to use -- the confusion being caused by the decision to let the underlying action buttons have their action activated when becoming the new state instead of when being changed from. As a result, this button is considered to have "inverted" behavior. Though this button implementation remains completely functional as intended, it is recommended to use SwitchButton instead.
  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    com.github.xemiru.sponge.boxboy.util.MenuPattern.apply(Menu, boolean)
    Underscores can now be used to represent slots that should forcibly be emptied. MenuPattern.apply(Menu) can be used after giving the pattern underscores instead.
    com.github.xemiru.sponge.boxboy.button.Button.isAnimated()
    While still usable for special implementations of non-static representatives through the use of Button.getRepresentative(), it is recommended to implement Button.getAnimatedRepresentative() instead.
    com.github.xemiru.sponge.boxboy.button.ToggleButton.of(ActionButton, ActionButton)
    see ToggleButton
    com.github.xemiru.sponge.boxboy.button.ToggleButton.of(ActionButton, ActionButton, boolean)
    see ToggleButton
